up in babylon ny where her father owned the tempus fugit antique store and her mother was a reference librarian schapiro graduated from babylon high school and matriculated at franklin  marshall college where she was graduated in  in  she earned a juris doctor jd degree with honors from george washington university law school career prior to the secedit schapiro was appointed in  by president ronald reagan to fill one of two democratic seats on the sec president george h w bush reappointed her to this position in  president bill clinton appointed schapiro acting chair of the sec and then appointed her chair of the commodity futures trading commission in  in  schapiro joined the national association of securities dealers nasd now the financial industry regulatory authority as the president of nasd regulation in  she became the vice chair of the nasd in  schapiro oversaw a widereaching probe into giftgiving and entertaining on wall street uncovering several instances of lavish and excessive activities which led to many charges in  she became nasds chair and ceo in that position she oversaw nasds consolidation with nyse member regulation to form the financial industry regulatory authority in january  president george w bush appointed schapiro to the member council of the presidents advisory council on financial literacy in  schapiro was named to investment advisor magazines ia  the list of the  most influential people in and around the investment advisory business in  her last year at finra schapiro earned a regular compensation package of  million on departure from finra she received additional lump sum retirement benefit payments to a total of just under  millionshe received  million as a final distribution including  million in vested retirement benefits according to a finra report she makes  at the sec sec chairedit in january  the us senate unanimously confirmed schapiros appointment by president barack obama to be the secs first female permanent chair schapiro partially blamed the financial crises of  on deregulation telling senators that the regulatory system had not kept pace with the markets and the needs of investors as the secs head she said she would press for tighter regulation of financial instruments including derivatives during schapiros tenure at the sec the agency improved its enforcement program creating new structures procedures and programs to better address the modern financial markets including bringing  enforcement actions in fy  and a near record of  actions in fy  obtaining more than  billion in ordered disgorgements and penalties since fy  prosecuting the largest insider trading scheme ever discovered winning a record  million fine in the civil case against the ceo of the galleon hedge fund and bringing financialcrisis related actions against fannie mae and freddie mac among others also during schapiro’s tenure the sec brought a record number of enforcement actions and returned more than  billion to harmed investors schapiro also led the agency through one of its most active rulemaking periods and enacted many other investor protection measures including adopting more than three quarters of the rules required by the doddfrank act an early setback for schapiro as sec chair occurred in september  when us district judge jed rakoff rejected the secs proposed  million settlement with bank of america boa had been charged with failure to disclose bonuses paid to merrill lynch executive before the two companies merged under the settlements terms boa was allowed to deny any wrongdoing which they did when pressed by rakoff on the matter of guilt rakoff said the settlement did not comport with the most elementary notions of justice and morality seven months later rakoff approved a  million settlement of the boa case boa did not have to change its declaration of innocence upon schapiros departure from the sec in december  president obama commended schapiros contributions as chair in an official white house statement subsequent careeredit in april  schapiro joined promontory financial group where she is advisory board vice chair in  she joined the board of directors of general electric and in  she joined the board of directors of the london stock exchange group in  she was elected to the board of directors of cvs health personal lifeedit schapiro is married to charles chas cadwell a former official with the us small business administration they have two daughters she serves as treasurer of the humane rescue alliance formerly the washington humane society referencesedit  a b c d sec biographychairman mary l schapiro secgov retrieved  june    a b aruna viswanatha november   schapiro stepping down at sec walter to step in reuters   obama taps veteran regulator to head underfire sec agence france presse december   accessed february    the  most powerful women forbes august     meet washingtons newest watchdog bloomberg businessweek october     nominations hearing record us senate committee on agriculture nutrition  forestry june   httpsarchiveorgstreamnominationsheariunitnominationsheariunitdjvutxt  httpwiltondailyvoicecomnewsmarysusanhallschapiroofwilton  babylon beacon sept   httpwwwbabylonbeaconcomnewscolumnistshtmlprint  wilton daily voice obituary august    lavan rosie december   secs new chairman who is mary schapiro the times london   biography of schapiro archived  at the wayback machine finra  james j green may   watch list mark tibergien the consultant and now executive who taught advisors to think of their practices as businesses leads the ia  for  investment advisor retrieved    courtney comstock october   whoa finra paid mary schapiro  million in  business insider   alexis leondis and zeke faux jun   investors may lose as congress saves money on adviser oversight bloombergcom retrieved  march    labaton stephen january   sec nominee offers plan for tighter regulation the new york times   jennifer liberto november   sec chief mary schapiro to step down cnnmoneycom   th